.TH has_il 3
.SH NAME
\*Lhas_il\*O \- Determines whether insert/delete line is available
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lbool has_il(\|)\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "has_il subroutine"
.iX "has_il subroutine" "deleteln subroutine"
.iX "has_il subroutine" "insertln macro"
This function will return the value TRUE
if the terminal has insert line and delete line capabilities, or
if it can simulate them using scrolling regions.  This function
might be used to check if it would be appropriate to turn on
physical scrolling using the \*Lscrollok\*O routine.
.PP
The routines \*Linsertln\*O and \*Ldeleteln\*O are always
available in the \*Lcurses\*O library if the terminal does
not have the required facilities.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
This function returns TRUE if the terminal has insert line and
delete line capabilities, or can simulate them using
scrolling regions; otherwise it returns FALSE.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Ldeleteln\*O(3), \*Linsertln\*O(3), \*Lscrollok\*O(3)
.EQ
delim off
.EN
